{"word":"ἐνάγω","slug":"ἐνάγω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐνάγω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ξω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to lead in</i> or <i>on</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>inducere</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; mostly <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <el>μαίνεσθαι ἐνάγει ἀνθρώπους</el> (<a href='S:scilicet'>sc.</a> Bacchus) <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <i>to urge on, promote</i>, <el>τὸν πόλεμον</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}